cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

The paper deals with a visual recognition problem and proposes a method for fine-tuning and compressing a pre-trained convolutional network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization techniques and deep learning, which are relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the highly parameterized nature of state-of-the-art pruning methods, which is related to the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
